> I am converting my '64 Std to 12V and drove the original bushing out
> with a 9mm socket on an extension. It seemed to be in tightly. However
> the new "6V-to-12V" bushing I got from WW just slides right in.

This may not be good.  The point of the bushing is to provide a durable
wear surface for the shaft to ride on, but if the bushing turns in the
case, it will wear the soft case material away.

